<section class="brand--ministry-of-defence brand__border-color organisation__brand-border-top organisation__section-wrap organisation__margin-bottom" id="featured-documents">
  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--padding gem-c-heading--margin-bottom-2  ">Featured</h2>

    </div>
  </div>


    <div class="grid-row">
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="The Reverend Nathan King conducts the rededication service for Lieutenant Donnelly. MOD Crown Copyright. " src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/69657/s465_The_Reverend_Nathan_King_conducts_the_rededication_service_for_Lieutenant_Donnelly.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2019-03-22">22 March 2019</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>News story</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/graves-of-two-irish-soldiers-killed-during-the-great-war-are-rededicated-a-century-later">Graves of two Irish Soldiers killed during the Great War are rededicated a century later</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>The resting places of Lieutenant (Lt) Gilbert Donnelly and Captain (Capt) John Forsythe Harvey, were honoured on Thursday 21 March during two rededication services held at the Commonwealth War Graves Commission’s (CWGC) Ste. Emilie Valley Cemetery and Noyon New British Cemetery in France.</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
  </div>

        </div>
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="The bearer party from The Royal Irish Regiment, led by WO2 Gary Wilkins, lower the coffin (taken at the Wednesday 20 March service)" src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/69640/s465_s300_Photo_1_-_Crown_Copyright.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2019-03-21">21 March 2019</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>News story</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/four-unknown-irish-soldiers-buried-one-hundred-years-after-their-deaths-in-the-great-war">Four unknown Irish soldiers buried 100 years after their deaths in The Great War</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>Two burial services have taken place on the Western Front honouring four unknown Irish soldiers who fell  during the First World War</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
  </div>

        </div>
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="An example of the new Veterans ID card, Crown Copyright" src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/68991/s465_s300_vets_id_card.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2019-02-18">18 February 2019</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>News story</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/new-veterans-id-cards-rolled-out-to-service-leavers">New veterans ID cards rolled out to service leavers</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>All service leavers will receive a new ID card to mark their time in the armed forces.</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
  </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-row">
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="Logos, Copyright kings College London, KCMHR, University of Oxford, Lancaster University and the Medical Research Council, All rights reserved" src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/68976/s465_Logo1.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2019-02-18">18 February 2019</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>News story</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/new-research-on-the-long-term-health-of-2-groups-of-older-veterans">New research on the long term health of 2 groups of older veterans</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>Researchers from King’s College London, University of Oxford and Lancaster University are planning new research investigating whether past exposure to small doses of chemical warfare agents impact long term health.</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
  </div>

        </div>
        <div class="column-one-third">
